###########################################
bare react app for forking

if running from the fresh react image, these two install steps are already done
npm install --save-dev parcel
npm install react react-dom

start sever with:
  rm -rf .parcel-cache && npx parcel {-p 1236 or whatever port you set up in docker}
  or
  rm -rf .parcel-cache && npx parcel src/index.html {-p 1236 or whatever port you set up in docker}
  (if you haven't added that to package.json)



this is really useful:
  npm i -g new-component

(it's Josh's instant dir and boilerplate for new components)
